article.headline: Norfolk St. 87, N.C. Central 83
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Michael Deloach sank a jumper with 30 seconds to go Monday and Norfolk State handed N.C. Central its 20th defeat, 87-83. The Spartans (4-8) led through much of the first half before a three-pointer by Bryan Ayala put N.C. Central (1-20) ahead. N.C. Central held onto the lead for the next three minutes until a jumper by Corey Lyons again put the Spartans ahead. The Spartans led 51-37 going into the half. The Eagles were determined in the second half and Ayala added to his game total 26 points to help chip away at Norfolk's lead. Tied at 79-79 with 1:44 on the clock, the Eagles added a free throw and took the lead. But shots from Deloach sealed Norfolk's win. Corey Lyons and Tony Murphy each had 22 for Norfolk.
